I"’<p>Neural workspace theory argues that attention is based on a competitive process which involves <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/consciousness-as-latent-representation-store-is-consonant-with-experiential-insights">multiple simultaneous stimuli and feature dimensions</a>. It argues that firing synchrony is the main mechanism deciding the winners in this <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/representationism-in-cognition-is-adaptationism-in-evolution">selection process pressured by relevance</a> through phase-locking, together with <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/perception-is-context-dependent">various biases</a>.</p>
